_sText: This has been in development for a while now, and I think it's finally time that it is released to the public, don't you? ^_^ STORY: It's short this time around. A city in turmoil! In the process of shutting down due to contamination, local officials have left behind a bunch of employees working overtime at the storage facility across the road. Blocked in and with no where else to go, the employees must now hold out against the impending zombie horde and hope for the best. FEATURES: - 25+ areas to climb, camp, and barricade. - Breakable doors and windows that lead to new areas. - Ventilation system that connects various buildings and areas together to promote balanced gameplay. - Various secrets and surprises. - A unique, close-quarters landscape and atmosphere which is sure to get your heart racing. - Custom textures. OTHER INFORMATION: * BSP FILE SIZE: Under 4MB This map is recommended for a server of 16-24 players, but the map will support up to 32 players quite comfortably. 64 player servers are not supported as there are only 32 player spawns. 64 players was indeed tested, but it simply didn't work; the map isn't large enough to hold that many players, so support was removed for it. I worked very diligently on this map for a solid two months. I hope that my hard work shows. It took three hours straight before players even started to RTV this on my server, so I recommend you test out this map in-game first before assessing or anything, as my screenshots simply don't do it justice. The source VMF file is included in the download. This means you can open up Hammer yourself anytime to go and edit the map. Feel free to make your own versions and remixes of this map if you so desire, as long as you give me full credit for my work. As always, comments, assessments, and stamps are more than welcome. When assessing however, please make yourself clear and provide examples of what's wrong, otherwise I'm just going to think all you want are the points. Thanks and enjoy, everyone. =D

ZM_ECHO_ITALY_RELOADED Created By: £cho, Valve Completion Time: 30hrs. Maximum Players: 64 Recommended Player Count: 24-32 Last Version: zm_echo_italy_b1 CLICK HERE TO VIEW OLD VERSION OF MAP This map has been drastically improved since zm_echo_italy_b1, and after some serious hardcore testing, the latest version is now ready for public release. In this version 95% of ugly graphical skybox errors have been fixed, there are no longer random boundaries (players can go nearly where ever they'd like on the map). the barricading spots are now balanced, new climbing areas have been added, lighting has been changed, the map fully optimized, and there's even a new secret! That was a mouthful I know, but it's been a while since I've gotten to submit a normal ZM map to FPSB, so I really wanted to make this one special. Anyhow, try out the map for yourself. The screenshots do some glory, but playtesting it is really the best way to know for sure if the map is good or not. If you like it and have a server, add it and see what the players think. If you already have zm_echo_italy_b1 on your servers, update it with this version and everyone is sure to like it a hell of a lot better! As always, comments, assessments, and stamps are always welcome. Thanks for reading and enjoy the map! Regards, £cho

A completely reworked cs_italy, designed for ZombieMod. It's a quick release, but I've added over 20+ climbing areas, and expanded the map with brand-new areas, and even a couple of secret ones. The map has an even better frame rate then it ever has before thanks to my optimizing methods. 

The screenshots show just some of the newest additions to the map, but trust me, there's many more than I can show you. So, by all means, download the map and test it yourself. There's some minor graphical glitches in the map involving the skybox, but nothing that harms gameplay. 

This is a beta release, but I expect to get a final out sooner rather than later, as there's not much I expect to change from this release other than bugs and those graphical errors I was talking about.


Enjoy the map, everyone.
Comments and assessments are more than welcome.
Big thanks to Valve for such a great map.

Regards,
£cho

== ZM_DUSTPANIC_B3 ==

B3 release of the map.  Fixes all the exploits from ZM_dustpanic_b2.

This is a loose remake & remix of the classic ZM map "lila_panic".  It doesn't follow the original design or layout very closely, so while the map is obviously inspired by Lila_panic I've given it my own twists.  
Also, as the name suggests, this map is made in the theme of DE_DUST.

The map has been designed with balance in mind!  It should not be dominated by CTs or by zombies - both teams should be able to move around fluidly throughout the map, and camping spots are not impossible for zombies to reach up to.

Features full HDR, Colour Correction (new in B3), Cubemapping, 64 Spawnpoints, and Net Optimization (this map should not lag).

Simply extract this to your CStrike/maps folder.  No additional files are needed!


Special thanks to Jb_gamble, Eastsider and Gargantua for feedback!

Ok, this is simply just an optimized version of V2.

People at the TAG zm server complained about the lag, so I did my best to try and optimize it. I added a couple of areaportalwindows in the map to help block out uneeded rendering. I added fade distances to every prop so that they disappear when you get far enough away. I tried to my best to specify the distances corresponding to the map's structure. There may be rare occasions where you see a prop randomly disappear because of the specified distances.

I know this sucks, but I converted it to dev textures. The reason being that they are not as hard to render, making the performance ultimately better.


I added one tiny little addition to the concrete building. It has a pathway around it's mid-section that has 3 small rooms you can get in. I don't know if it's useful, but someone is bound to discover some sort of crazy thing that makes it good.

Well, I don't think I released the first version, but if you go to [TAG]=>Zombie Infection server, you probably played it once or twice, depending on your timing. But this is the newest release. It is similar to lila_panic. There is an outdoor area, much bigger than lila_panics, though. And then there is a basement. The basement area was created by TheFrog, who is also registered here. He can go by either that or Darth, I believe. But anyway, the map is pretty big. Hopefully the gameplay is balanced out pretty well, and there aren't any cheap spots.

Hate vents? Hooray for you, this map has NO vents. Vents suck.
